            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell halign="left">C  D  G</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell halign="left">Suspended 4th</cell>
            <cell>Csus4</cell>
            <cell>C</cell>
            <cell>F*</cell>
            <cell>G</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell halign="left">C  F  G</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell halign="left">Dom. 7th sus4</cell>
            <cell>C7sus4</cell>
            <cell>C</cell>
            <cell>F*</cell>
            <cell>G</cell>
            <cell>B<flat /></cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell halign="left">C  F  G  B<flat /></cell>
          </row>
          <row bottom="major">
            <cell halign="left">Maj. 7th sus4</cell>
            <cell>Cmaj7sus4</cell>
            <cell>C</cell>
            <cell>F*</cell>
            <cell>G</cell>
            <cell>B</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell>—</cell>
            <cell halign="left">C  F  G  B</cell>
          </row>
        </tabular>
      </table>
      <p>
        Parentheses ( ) indicate a note that is theoretically present but commonly omitted in 
        practice. An asterisk * in the <q>3/sus</q> column indicates a suspended note replacing 
        the third: D (2nd degree) for sus2, F (4th degree) for sus4.
      </p>
    </conclusion>
  </section>

</chapter>
